comments.body:
Thanks [~xgong] for delivering a patch. The patch looks good in overall. Some comments on issues of exception handling:
In NMWebServices.java,
{code}
+            try {
+              LogToolUtils.outputAggregatedContainerLog(nmContext.getConf(),
+                  appId, appOwner, containerId.toString(),
+                  nmContext.getNodeId().toString(), outputFileName, bytes,
+                  os, buf);
+            } catch (Exception ex) {
+              // Something wrong when we try to access the aggregated log,
+              // simply ignore it.
             }
{code}
Shall we log a warn here if accessing aggregated log? I think that could be helpful for trouble shooting. Isn't it? Also, do we need to close os which output stream? I haven't check if caller have similar logic. If we already have, we can skip here.


{code}
+    final ContainerId containerId = tempContainerId;
+    boolean tempIsRunning = false;
+    // check what is the status for container
+    try {
+      Container container = nmContext.getContainers().get(containerId);
+      tempIsRunning = (container.getContainerState() == ContainerState.RUNNING);
+    } catch (Exception ex) {
+      // This NM does not have this container any more. We
+      // assume the container has already finished. Ignore the
+      // exception.
+    }
{code}
This is warn by findbugs also. We should log something (debug or warn level depends on if expected) for trouble shooting. Also, if container is not found, we should skip the following code and return directly.

Other looks fine. btw, unit test failure seems not related and being tracked in other JIRA.

